description:
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Acute Oncology Sister/Charge Nurse&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 6&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;(22.5 hours per week)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen to join the Acute Oncology Service in St Lukes Cancer Centre, Royal Surrey County Hospital. &lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; We are seeking a committed, dynamic, motivated individual with an interest in developing and improving Acute Oncology services, who also has exceptional communication and interpersonal skills to join a dedicated and cohesive team within this specialty. The post holder will play a central role within the Acute Oncology Services multi-disciplinary teams working closely with existing medical and nursing colleagues; providing specialist nursing contribution to the clinical management of cancer patients needing emergency care, enabling prompt assessment, diagnosis and treatment, not only when developing complications of chemotherapy but also when admitted with consequences of their cancer; supporting the management of patients with a previously undiagnosed cancer who present as an emergency and through traditional routes of referral. Ensuring patients and carers receive holistic, multi-faceted support, coordinated care, and all the information they need, throughout the course of their illness is essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate must demonstrate an aptitude for working independently. The work will encompass assessing patient’s needs when admitted as an emergency, attending Ward Rounds and MDT’s, in particular providing specialist support and advice on the management of cancer patients presenting acutely, with cancer of unknown primary and suspected cancer. You will provide specialist evidence based nursing to patients in managing complications and side-effects of treatments and cancer related conditions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further details or an informal visit, please contact Sam Russell (Lead Acute Oncology Nurse) Nurse 01483 571122 ex 2479. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
